Logical Operators

   And Or Not
   && || !
   We use them when we have two or more conditions to test .
  And
  true && true=> true
  true && false=> false
  false && true=>false
  false && false=>false


  boolean sold=true;
     boolean rain=true;

     if(cold){
     SOpln(" I will stay at home");

     }



  OR
    true || true=> true
    true || false=> true
    false || true=>true
    false || false=>false



   boolean sold=true;
   boolean rain=true;

   if(cold){
   SOpln(" I will stay at home");

   }




Switch Statement :

is an alternative of  if else if

syntax of switch statement

switch (variable) {

// value must be the same date type as variable

case value1:
    code A;
    break;
case value2:
    code B;
    break;
default:
    code C;
    break;



}




